  "text": "Consider a time-varying number of targets (max of 10) moving with nonconstant velocity as shown in Fig. 4 . Note that targets 1-6 are born at time , targets 7-10 are born at time , and targets 3-4 die at time . The starting and stopping positions for each track are labelled with a circle and triangle, respectively. The multi-target filters used to test the new metric are the Gaussian mixture PHD [CITATION_1] and Gaussian mixture CPHD [CITATION_2] filters. Although it is not our primary intention here to examine these filters in detail, we note that the former is known to have much higher variance on its estimate of the number of targets than the latter.",
